data.message: Hello, this morning I posted a photo of my pregnancy progression. Someone reported it for nudity. Facebook deemed it acceptable but almost immediately after that another photo, from May was reported and minutes later the original photo was reported again. These are all photos from my timeline, most recently a photo of weight loss comparison, in which I'm clothes was reported. This photo wasn't on my timeline it was in a separate album, from 2012.  My page it private so only friends should be able to see my photos. How do I manage this. I want to remove and block this person for falsely reporting my photos, or find out if it is a bot. but there is no way to find out who they are
